# Route files

Routes **compose**; they do not implement.

## Required shape

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — post.tsx target pattern
import { createFileRoute } from '@tanstack/react-router'
import { FeaturePage } from '../features/post/post-page'

export const Route = createFileRoute('/post')({
  loader: ({ context }) => context.queryClient.ensureQueryData(postQueryOptions()),
  component: PostRoute,
})

function PostRoute() {
  const data = Route.useLoaderData()
  return <FeaturePage {...data} />
}
```

## Forbidden in routes

- Inline forms >20 lines → extract component
- `createServerFn` definitions → `app/server/{domain}.ts`
- OAuth/business logic → `app/lib/server/`
- Onboarding wizards, modals, guides → `app/components/` or `app/features/onboarding/`

## Refactor legacy bloat

`app/routes/index.tsx` (~1500 lines) is technical debt. New work goes in extracted modules; do not add to the monolith.

When touching a route over 150 lines, extract at least one chunk in the same PR.
